"{\"uid\": \"theolivepress.es-spain-news-2024-07-29-rafael-nadal-v-novak-djokovic-at-the-olympics-2024-this-is-when-the-two-rivals-will-clash-in-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"RAFAEL Nadal will face off against old foe Novak Djokovic in a mouth-watering second round clash in the Paris 2024 Olympics men's singles this afternoon.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The great old rivals will play their 60th competitive game against each other after 1.30pm CET on Monday - Djokovic currently narrowly leads the head-to-head with 30 wins to the Spaniard's 29, although Nadal will hold court advantage as he seeks to get back on level terms.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 357, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4515031551800472e-11, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two will play at Roland Garros, a clay court that has played host to Nadal's 14 French Open titles, in a match widely regarded as one 'last dance' for a pair acclaimed as two of the sport's best ever players and who have won a combined 46 Grand Slam titles.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1212581480383691e-13, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4515031551800472e-11, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal, now 38, had cast doubt on his participation thanks to a niggling thigh injury.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"?\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"?pic.twitter.com/BDuYZtgs2r  But the 2008 gold medalist secured his passage to Monday's second round tie after beating Hungary's Marton Fucsovics 6-1, 4-6, 6-4, much to the delight of the French crowd.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.7950810360732087, \"rank\": 0.25772663726220413, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\", \"score\": 0.9999999956035026, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marton Fucsovics\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\"}, {\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.856764114372137, \"rank\": 0.16688609830095547, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia's Djokovic, 37, advanced to the second round thanks to a 6-0, 6-1 victory over Australia's Matt Ebden.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999259157879965, \"rank\": 7.405207491531763e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.047790656356555e-13, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 1070, \"end\": 1079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9996449224905936, \"rank\": 0.0003433166236753486, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Ebden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Spain's highly-anticipated duo of Nadal and 21-year-old Carlos Alcaraz won their men's doubles first round against the Argentine sixth seeds Maximo Gonzalez and Andres Molteni 7-6, 6-4.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999938044062243, \"rank\": 6.1956300525312444e-06, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedi